headline: Patient Engagement in Genomics Research Fuels Growth in Healthcare Segment
summary: The global genomics market is set to expand from USD 47.07 billion in 2025 to USD 85.09 billion by 2030, with a CAGR of 12.6%. Driven by increased government funding, rising disease prevalence, and advances in NGS technologies, the market sees augmented application in healthcare, agriculture, and forensics.
